"A
lady!
That
has
quite
a
romantic
twang.
We
must
guess
who
it
is.
Rosy,
whisper
the
name
low
to
your
father.
Don't
let
him
hear."
"Rose,
don't
be
too
forward
to
talk,"
here
interrupted
Mrs.
Yorke,
in
her
usual
kill
joy
fashion,
"nor
Jessy
either.
It
becomes
all
children,
especially
girls,
to
be
silent
in
the
presence
